HEADWORD: on-duty
<hw>on-duty</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>performing or available for
duties; <as>as, her <ex>on-duty</ex> hours were 11p.m. to 7 a.m.</as>.
Opposite of <ant>off-duty</ant>.</def> <mark>[prenominal]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> on duty(predicate).</syn>⟦br⟧
